quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,11,"And He Who sent down water from the sky in due proportion, whereby We revived a lifeless land; thus you<sup>pl </sup>are brought out{1}.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Zekwan, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i, Ya’qub and Khalaf read it as: “…thus you come out.”]
  43,12,"And He Who created all pairs and provided you<sup>pl </sup>with ships and livestock on which you ride,"
  43,13,"that you<sup>pl </sup>may mount their backs then remember the blessing of your Lord as you settle upon them and say, “Highly Exalted is the One Who has subjected this to us, and in no way could we have done it by ourselves,"
  43,14,"and indeed to our Lord we are certainly returning.”"
  43,15,"Yet they ascribed to Him a portion of His servants. Surely, man is indeed an evidently staunch denier."
  43,16,"Or has He chosen for Himself daughters from what He creates, and favored you<sup>pl </sup>with sons?"
  43,17,"Yet when one of them is given glad tidings{1}of what he ascribed to the All-Merciful, his face becomes dark as he suppresses his anguish,",footnotes:1:[This is said in sarcasm.]
  43,18,"<i>(thinking) </i>“What! Someone brought up{1}amid adornments and, in conflict, cannot be evident?”{2}",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “Someone growing up amid…”],footnotes:2:[Pagans looked at women in a demeaning way.]
  43,19,"And they considered the angels, who are servants{1}ofthe All-Merciful, to be females. Did they witness{2}their creation? Their claim will be recorded and they will be asked.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Ibn Amer, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “…who are with the All-Merciful…”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “Were they made to witness their creation?”]
  43,20,"And they said, “Had the All-Merciful willed, we would not have worshiped them.” But they have no knowledge of that; they are merely conjecturing."
  43,21,"Or have We brought them a scripture prior to this one{1}, so that they are adhering to it?",footnotes:1:[The Qur’an.]
  43,22,"Rather, they said, “Indeed, we found our forefathers on a course{1}, and indeed we are being guided in their footsteps.”",footnotes:1:[Literally, ‘a nation: a community’.]
